I have started updating my dataflows to use the new API since the betas are getting deprecated in two days and I have a quick question.

Previously on the v1beta* this is how you'd set a limit to a query on DatastoreIO reader:

    import com.google.datastore.v1.Query;
			
	Query.Builder query_builder = Query.newBuilder();
    query_builder.addKindBuilder().setName("Kind");
	query_builder.setLimit(500000);
	Query query = query.build();

Now on V1 setLimit no longer takes an Int as an argument, but an Int32Value object.

Is this how it should go now?

    import com.google.datastore.v1.Query;
